parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates or flashes on the dashboard
indicating a faulty airbag system; the airbag system may not deploy in the event of an accident.

indicating a faulty airbag sensor; the airbag system may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and even catch fire, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Smell of burning rubber
smoke or fire coming from the alternator
difficulty starting the vehicle
battery light and brake light on the dashboard
clicking noise in the wiring
loss of electrical power
and the vehicle stalling or dying while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or catch fire, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clicking noise in the wiring
loss of electrical power
battery light and brake light on the dashboard
smell of burning rubber
smoke or fire coming from the alternator
and the vehicle stalling or dying while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to include certain VINs in the recall campaign can lead to vehicles with faulty alternators or electrical systems remaining on the road, posing a risk to drivers and passengers.
symptoms: Same as Alternator Failure and Electrical System Failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Dead battery
difficulty starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear light panel can cause reduced visibility, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Rear light panel failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to not slow down properly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The ABS system kicks in but does not properly slow the vehicle
the ABS braking system light comes on the dashboard
the vehicle idles roughly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake cable assembly can cause the brake cable to wear through or cut, leading to brake failure and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake cable rubs against the suspension
the brake cable wears through or cuts
brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leak of brake fluid can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
defective gasket.
